summary: I have skills and experience in the education sector ranging from ECE through to tertiary. I am currently working in Tokelau as an education facilitator, primarily supporting all to raise academic achievement with learners from ECE through to secondary level. My previous role included working as a HoD ESOL catering for migrants in a secondary school, mainstream setting. My experience prior to this role was in the special needs field catering for moderate needs learners. This included setting up individualized programs, group programs and PLD for teaching staff to support their at risk learners. During this time, I was also studying part time to keep abreast of current research in the ESOL and Special needs field. I started studies in the leadership field and am yet to complete this field. I have lectured at Auckland University part time as a Pacifika Education lecturer. My passion is supporting teachers, learners and their communities in proactive education measures. I am a competitive squash player and enjoy socializing with people from different backgrounds.
